      "question": "Find the roots of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 11x + 24 = 0$ by the method of factorisation.",
      "answer": "$x = 3$ and $x = 8$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify two numbers whose product is $24$ and whose sum is $-11$. These numbers are $-8$ and $-3$.",
          "Split the middle term $-11x$ into $-8x - 3x$ and factorise by grouping to solve for $x$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 - 11x + 24 = 0 \\\\ x^2 - 8x - 3x + 24 = 0 \\\\ x(x - 8) - 3(x - 8) = 0 \\\\ (x - 8)(x - 3) = 0 \\\\ x - 8 = 0 \\text{ or } x - 3 = 0 \\\\ x = 8, x = 3$"
      },
